Jimmy Godden https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimmy_Godden 0 Jimmy Godden (11 August 1879 – 5 March 1955) was a British film actor.He was educated at Christ's Hospital and was in the Civil Service before becoming a concert pianist. Godden later turned to the stage and made his debut in pantomime at the Theatre Royal, Plymouth, then going on to the London West End doing a number of comedies and revues.
